The President issued a statement recognizing the celebration of Diwali, the festival of lights, by Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and some Buddhists. He mentioned that he was the first President to mark Diwali at the White House and that he and Michelle had joined in Diwali celebrations during their visit to India. The President highlighted that Diwali is a time for gathering with family and friends, enjoying good food and dancing. He also emphasized the importance of contemplation and prayer, as well as the obligation to help the less fortunate. The President concluded by wishing everyone observing the holiday a Happy Diwali and Saal Mubarak.